    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - 3300 Model - ELECTRONIC GAUGE CLUSTER - DIAGNOSTICS - GAUGE DATA
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="0">
        <title>GAUGE DATA</title>
        <para>The EGC continuously monitors incoming gauge data for out-of-range or data-not-present conditions. If the
            data is out of range, the Cluster or gauge pack will turn on the LED embedded in the respective gauge.
        </para>
        <para>Missing data to a small gauge in the EGC will cause the needle to be driven clockwise to the 6 o'clock
            position. Missing data to the speedometer or tachometer will cause the gauge to repeat the following three
            times:
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Go immediately to the zero position</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Sweep up to the 50% position</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Sweep back to zero</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Pause</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
    </svcproc>
